      <td valign="bottom"><big><big><font face="Arial">Huggin's Event at Grimoire, Tomorrow Night!       </font></big></big></td>
      <td valign="bottom" align="right">
      
      </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td colspan="2"><table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="100%">
        <tr>
          <td><font face="Arial">by <a href='mailto:fear@battlevortex.com'>Cardinal Fear</a>
          </font></td>
          <td><p align="right"><font face="Arial"><small>posted 11/4/99 8:20:54 PM
          </small></font></td>
        </tr>
      </table>
      </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td colspan="2"><font face="Arial"><br>Huggin’s Weekend event at Grimoire Arena.  <BR>Friday November 5th, @ (9 PM PST, 10 PM MST, 11 PM Central, Midnight EST) <BR>Sponsored by SI and Grimoire.<BR>1 on 1 Event. <BR><BR>Here are the rules:<BR><BR>·	No magic items.<BR>·	Max 5 greater heal potions 3 of any other for a total of 8. You may not make anymore during the battle.<BR>·	No pre- poisoned weapons. They may be poisoned during the battle<BR>·	Healing, barding, magery, and Archery, are allowed.<BR>·	No use of summoning spells, blade spirits, energy vortex, recall or gate<BR>·	Up to three trapped bags/chests to break paralyze.  They may be re-trapped during the battle<BR><BR>Entry fee is 3,000 GP if you pre-register 5,000 if you register at the event. To pre-register ICQ Huggin at ICQ #6773255.<BR><BR>To avoid confusion, registration will start at 8 PM PST, and end at 9:10 PM PST and no late entries.<BR><BR>Grand Prize this week is 20,000 GP. Winner takes all, 2nd place gets mentioned.<BR><BR>Non-combatants are welcome to come and enjoy the contest. However, there are several important rules which must be followed at all times. Failure to do so can result in your untimely demise and banishment from the arena:<BR><BR>·	There is to be NO talking during the contest. Talking and movement contributes to lag. If you wish to speak with someone, either do it outside of the game or take it outside of the tavern. Anyone talking will first be removed; if you continue to talk, you will be banned.<BR><BR>·	There is to be NO moving around while the combatants are fighting. This is for<BR>the same reason as stated above. The staff will remove any non-combatant moving during the fight.<BR><BR>·	Stay out of the combat arena. Persons who leave the one square area circling the arena will be assumed to be there to loot or interfere with the combat. Policy when dealing with such offenses is to kill the person to prevent loot from leaving the arena, and then to ban the ghost.<BR><BR>·	Staff will resurrect any fallen combatants. Do not attempt to resurrect anyone, as it will be assumed that you are trying to loot the corpse. Anyone moving towards the body will be dealt with as described above.<BR><BR>·	If you are capable of hiding, please do so. Hidden players help reduce the effects of lag during the fights.<BR><BR>·	If you do have a horse, you must stable it with the animal tamer to help reduce Lag. Make sure you have 30 GP in your account or in your pack to ‘stable’ your mount. You can ‘claim’ your mount after the event. Please do not bring any other pets!<BR><BR>We hope to see you at the fights! If you have any questions or comments, feel<BR>free to ICQ me at 6773255<BR><BR>Huggins Tentative Schedule:<BR>Friday, November 12th @ (9 PM PST, 10 PM MST, 11 PM Central, Midnight EST) Bar Fight.<BR>Friday, November 19th, @ (9 PM PST, 10 PM MST, 11 PM Central, Midnight EST) 2 vs. 2 Combat.<BR>Friday November 26th, @ (9 PM PST, 10 PM MST, 11 PM Central, Midnight EST) 1 vs. 1 Warrior Skills.<BR>Friday December 3rd, @ (9 PM PST, 10 PM MST, 11 PM Central, Midnight EST) 1vs 1 Elimination Event.<BR><BR>For details on other events, rules, maps and community message board, please visit: http://www.battlevortex.com/grimoire/<BR><P><a href='http://www.battlevortex.com/grimoire/'>Grimiore</a></P></td>
    </tr>

